{
  "texts": [
    "This poses high requirements for the design of RC network structures and training algorithms.",
    "Using other technologies such as super-resolution and compressive sensing to overcome the resolution problem of single-point measurement and processing in RC systems may be a viable solution.",
    "The second is the real-time data processing problem: One of the significant advantages of reservoir computing is lightweight and fast computation.",
    "However, in practical physical systems, it is often unrealistic to sample and store a large number of node responses to a certain input due to limitations such as sampling bandwidth, storage depth and bandwidth, or their combinations.",
    "It is simply not feasible in many cases to probe a system with a large number of probes (10s-1000s) interfaced with AD converters."
  ]
}